item.title: Leidos wins $64M FAA contract
item.description: The Federal Aviation Administration has awarded Reston-based Fortune 500 government contractor Leidos Holdings Inc. a $64 million contract to develop the Operational Analysis and Reporting System (OARS), a safety analysis tool. OARS will support the FAA’s Air Traffic Organization (ATO) Safety Management System though defining, identifying, assessing, treating and tracking safety risk mitigation.

item.description: The company will add 28 jobs with average salaries around $45,000 and will be the county's first large manufacturing employer in 20 years.

item.title: Virginia Beach to pay Dominion Energy $3.7 million to move equipment for surf park project
item.description: The power company's Atlantic substation sits on land owned by Norfolk Southern at the Oceanfront. Virginia Beach is negotiating to buy the parcel, but first needs Dominion Energy to vacate it.

item.title: 80,000 Virginians who lost unemployment while waiting for a hearing could see money return
item.description: Between April 1 and Sept. 30, Virginia had the worst rate in the United States for making an eligibility determination, doing so only 9% of the time within 21 days, according to federal data.
